<subSubSection id="C353655E697F7A2FDDA82ECD06D9FEF9" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="183" pageId="11" pageNumber="182" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF636D5697F7A2FDDA82ECD06D9FEF9" blockId="11.[163,1070,1430,1575]" lastBlockId="12.[163,1070,205,349]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="183" pageId="11" pageNumber="182">
Comparative notes:In the key in ASSING (2012a), 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D56697F7A28DE312ECC06F4FA08" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[826,956,1431,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitipennis">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC7697F7A28DE312ECC06F4FA08" box="[826,956,1431,1452]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="182">R. nitipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would key out at couplet 27, together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D56697F7A28DCEC2EED0647FA6F" authority="ASSING 2012" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2012" box="[487,783,1461,1483]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabripennis">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC7697F7A28DCEC2EED07CBFA6E" box="[487,643,1461,1483]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="182">R. glabripennis</emphasis>
ASSING 2012
</taxonomicName>
from northern 
<collectingRegion id="498DF837697F7A28DEA12EED06B5FA6F" box="[938,1021,1462,1483]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="11" pageNumber="182">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
. It is distinguished from this species by numerous characters, particularly the much darker legs (
<taxonomicName id="4C494D56697F7A28DDA02EA80403F9A3" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2012" box="[171,331,1522,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabripennis">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC7697F7A28DDA02EA80403F9A3" box="[171,331,1522,1544]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="182">R. glabripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: legs reddish with infuscate femoral apices), the distinctly less coarse and less confluent punctation of the head, the more shiny and more uneven surface of the head, the presence of a median shiny elevation on the pronotum (
<taxonomicName id="4C494D5669787A2FDE4F2B9606A9FF46" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2012" box="[836,993,205,226]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabripennis">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC769787A2FDE4F2B9606A9FF46" box="[836,993,205,226]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="183">R. glabripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: whole pronotum with coarse and very dense puncation, without impunctate band and without median elevation), the even longer and more shiny elytra, the more finely and less densely punctate, as well as more shiny abdomen, and by the completely different male sexual characters. For illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D5669787A2FDF2B2A1307F4FEF9" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2012" box="[544,700,328,349]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabripennis">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC769787A2FDF2B2A1307F4FEF9" box="[544,700,328,349]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="183">R. glabripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B2469787A2FDFE22A1C06C5FEF9" author="ASSING V" box="[745,909,327,349]" pageId="12" pageNumber="183" pagination="115 - 190" refId="ref11068" refString="ASSING V. (2012 a): The Rugilus species of the Palaearctic and Oriental regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde A, Neue Serie 5: 115 - 190." type="journal article" year="2012">ASSING (2012a)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C353655E69787A2FDDA82A350144FE65" pageId="12" pageNumber="183" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF636D569787A2FDDA82A350144FE65" blockId="12.[163,1070,366,450]" pageId="12" pageNumber="183">
Distribution and natural history:The type locality is situated in the Gaoligong Shan in the northwest of 
<collectingRegion id="498DF83769787A2FDF372AD507A6FE07" box="[572,750,397,419]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="12" pageNumber="183">Yunnan province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F35E764569787A2FDFF22AD60670FE07" box="[761,824,397,419]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="183">China</collectingCountry>
, not far from the border with 
<collectingCountry id="F35E764569787A2FDDDD2AF70474FE65" box="[214,316,428,449]" name="Myanmar" pageId="12" pageNumber="183">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
. The specimens were collected at an altitude of approximately 
<quantity id="4CB19B3069787A2FDEB22AF70140FE65" box="[953,1032,428,450]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="183" unit="m" value="3000.0">3000 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
